B.N2=new A.bK(B.d2,["TERMS OF SERVICE","Last updated: May 2026","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 TERMS OF SERVICE Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'1. DEFINITIONS\n\n  "Platform"        \u2014 The Infinity Kredits website, mobile application, and all related services. "Company" / "We"  \u2014 Infinity Kredits and its owners, operators, and assigns. "User" / "You"    \u2014 Any person who accesses or uses the Platform. "Digital Products"\u2014 In-game currency, app coins, gift cards, and other digital goods sold on the Platform. "Account"         \u2014 The registered user profile you create on the Platform. "Content"         \u2014 All text, images, data, and other material on the Platform.\n\n2. ELIGIBILITY\n\n  2.1  You must be at least 16 years of age to use the Platform. Users under 16 are strictly prohibited. See our Minor Safety Policy.\n\n  2.2  By using the Platform you represent and warrant that:\n         a) You are at least 16 years old;\n         b) You have the legal capacity to enter into a binding agreement;\n         c) You are not barred from using the Platform under any applicable law;\n         d) All information you provide is accurate and current.\n\n  2.3  Users aged 16\u201317 may require parental consent in certain jurisdictions.\n\n3. ACCOUNT REGISTRATION & SECURITY\n\n  3.1  To purchase Digital Products, you must create an Account. You agree to:\n         - Provide accurate, complete, and current registration information\n         - Keep your password confidential and not share it with anyone\n         - Notify us immediately of any unauthorised access to your Account\n         - Take responsibility for all activity occurring under your Account\n\n  3.2  We reserve the right to suspend or terminate Accounts that provide false information, violate these Terms, or engage in suspicious activity.\n\n  3.3  You may not create more than one Account without our prior written permission. Duplicate or fraudulent Accounts will be closed.\n\n4. DIGITAL PRODUCTS \u2014 PURCHASE & USE\n\n  4.1  All Digital Products sold on the Platform are:\n         - Delivered electronically\n         - Non-transferable (unless explicitly stated)\n         - For personal use only\n         - Subject to the terms of the relevant third-party game or application\n\n  4.2  Digital Products have no cash value and cannot be exchanged for real money except where explicitly stated and permitted by applicable law.\n\n  4.3  We act as a reseller of Digital Products. The use of those products within a game or application is governed by that game/app developer\'s own terms of service. We are not responsible for how third-party platforms handle your in-game assets.\n\n  4.4  You may not resell, trade, broker, or otherwise commercially exploit Digital Products purchased on our Platform without our explicit written consent.\n\n  4.5  Gift Cards purchased on the Platform are subject to our Gift Card Terms (see Section 10).\n\n5. PROHIBITED CONDUCT\n\nYou agree NOT to:\n\n  5.1  Use the Platform for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable law or regulation.\n\n  5.2  Engage in or facilitate fraud, money laundering, or any other financial crime.\n\n  5.3  Use stolen, compromised, or unauthorised payment methods.\n\n  5.4  Create Accounts using false or stolen identities.\n\n  5.5  Attempt to exploit, hack, reverse-engineer, or interfere with the Platform\'s security, systems, or databases.\n\n  5.6  Use automated scripts, bots, or tools to access, scrape, or manipulate the Platform.\n\n  5.7  Harass, threaten, or abuse other users or our staff.\n\n  5.8  Resell Digital Products in violation of Section 4.4.\n\n  5.9  Circumvent any technical measures designed to restrict or control Platform access.\n\n  5.10 Use the Platform if you are under 16 years of age.\n\nViolation of any of the above may result in immediate account termination, forfeiture of all balances and pending orders, and legal action.\n\n6. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\n\n  6.1  All content on the Platform \u2014 including logos, text, images, design, and software \u2014 is owned by or licensed to Infinity Kredits and is protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual-property laws.\n\n  6.2  You are granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to access and use the Platform for personal, non-commercial purposes only.\n\n  6.3  You may not copy, reproduce, modify, distribute, or create derivative works from any Platform content without our prior written permission.\n\n7. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES & LINKS\n\n  7.1  The Platform may contain links to third-party websites or services. We do not endorse, control, or take responsibility for third-party content, privacy practices, or terms of service.\n\n  7.2  Your interactions with third-party platforms (including game developers and app stores) are governed by those platforms\' own terms.\n\n  7.3  Infinity Kredits is an independent platform and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or officially connected to any game developer, publisher, or app company whose products we sell, unless explicitly stated.\n\n8. DISCLAIMERS & LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\n\n  8.1  THE PLATFORM AND ALL DIGITAL PRODUCTS ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.\n\n  8.2  WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT:\n         - The Platform will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure\n         - Digital Products will function as expected on all third-party platforms (including after game updates)\n         - Prices, product descriptions, or availability are error-free\n\n  8.3  TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, INFINITY KREDITS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR:\n         - Indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages\n         - Loss of profits, data, or goodwill\n         - Any damages arising from your use of or inability to use the Platform or Digital Products\n         - Actions or decisions taken by third-party game/app developers affecting Digital Products you have purchased\n\n  8.4  OUR TOTAL AGGREGATE LIABILITY TO YOU FOR ANY CLAIM ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THESE TERMS OR THE PLATFORM SHALL NOT EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID TO US IN THE 90 DAYS PRIOR TO THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM.\n\n  8.5  Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of implied warranties or limitation of liability. In such cases, our liability is limited to the fullest extent permitted by law.\n\n9. INDEMNIFICATION\n\nYou agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Infinity Kredits and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses (including legal fees) arising from:\n  - Your use of the Platform\n  - Your violation of these Terms\n  - Your violation of any third party\'s rights\n  - Any fraudulent, illegal, or harmful conduct by you\n\n10. GIFT CARD TERMS\n\n  10.1 Gift Cards sold on the Platform are valid for the denomination and brand stated at the time of purchase.\n\n  10.2 Gift Cards cannot be exchanged for cash unless required by law.\n\n  10.3 Infinity Kredits Gift Cards expire 12 months from the date of purchase unless otherwise stated.\n\n  10.4 Third-party gift cards (e.g., Google Play, iTunes, Steam) are governed by the issuing company\'s own gift-card terms.\n\n  10.5 Lost, stolen, or damaged gift cards will not be replaced.\n\n  10.6 Fraudulent or counterfeit gift cards will be voided and the associated Account may be terminated.\n\n11. ACCOUNT TERMINATION\n\n  11.1 You may close your Account at any time by contacting us at infinitykredits@gmail.com. Closing your Account does not entitle you to a refund of any unused balances unless required by applicable law.\n\n  11.2 We may suspend or terminate your Account at any time, with or without notice, if we believe you have violated these Terms or engaged in fraudulent, illegal, or harmful conduct.\n\n  11.3 Upon termination, your right to use the Platform ceases immediately. Provisions of these Terms that by their nature should survive termination (including Sections 8, 9, and 12) shall survive.\n\n12. GOVERNING LAW & DISPUTE RESOLUTION\n\n  12.1 These Terms are governed by the laws of India, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles.\n\n  12.2 Any dispute arising from or related to these Terms shall first be attempted to be resolved through good-faith negotiation by contacting us at infinitykredits@gmail.com.\n\n  12.3 If negotiation fails, disputes shall be submitted to binding arbitration under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (India), with proceedings conducted in English.\n\n  12.4 Notwithstanding the above, either party may seek injunctive or other equitable relief in a court of competent jurisdiction to prevent irreparable harm.\n\n  12.5 Users in the European Union retain the right to bring disputes before their local courts and applicable consumer protection bodies.\n\n13. CHANGES TO THESE TERMS\n\n  13.1 We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email and/or a notice on the Platform at least 14 days before the changes take effect.\n\n  13.2 Your continued use of the Platform after the effective date of any update constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.\n\n  13.3 If you do not agree to revised Terms, you must stop using the Platform and may close your Account.\n\n14. MISCELLANEOUS\n\n  14.1 Entire Agreement: These Terms, together with our Privacy Policy, Minor Safety Policy, Payments & Refund Policy, and any other policies published on the Platform, constitute the entire agreement between you and Infinity Kredits.\n\n  14.2 Severability: If any provision of these Terms is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.\n\n  14.3 No Waiver: Our failure to enforce any provision does not constitute a waiver of that provision.\n\n  14.4 Assignment: You may not assign your rights under these Terms. We may assign our rights and obligations without restriction.\n\n  14.5 Force Majeure: We are not liable for delays or failures caused by events beyond our reasonable control, including natural disasters, government actions, or infrastructure outages.\n\n15. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.MX=new A.bK(B.d2,["PRIVACY POLICY","Security and data handling","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 PRIVACY POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nInfinity Kredits ("Company," "we," "us," or "our") operates an online platform at which users may purchase in-game currency, application coins, gift cards, and other digital products (collectively, "Digital Products"). We are committed to protecting the privacy of every person who visits, registers on, or makes a purchase through our website, mobile application, or any other service we offer (collectively, the "Platform").\n\nThis Privacy Policy explains what personal information we collect, how we use and share it, how we protect it, and what rights you have over it. By accessing or using the Platform you agree to the practices described in this Policy.\n\nIf you do not agree with this Policy, please do not use the Platform.\n\n1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT\n\n1.1  Information You Provide Directly\n\n     a) Account Registration\n        - Full name\n        - Email address\n        - Username / display name\n        - Password (stored in hashed, salted form \u2014 never in plain text)\n        - Date of birth (used for age verification)\n        - Phone number (optional; used for two-factor authentication)\n\n     b) Purchase & Payment Information\n        - Billing name and address\n        - Payment card details (processed exclusively by PCI-DSS-compliant third-party payment processors; we do not store raw card numbers)\n        - UPI ID, wallet identifiers, or bank account details (where applicable)\n        - Transaction history and order IDs\n\n     c) Communications\n        - Messages sent to our customer support team\n        - Survey responses, feedback, or contest entries\n        - Content of any dispute or chargeback communications\n\n1.2  Information Collected Automatically\n\n     a) Usage Data\n        - Pages viewed, products browsed, search queries\n        - Timestamps of visits and session duration\n        - Links clicked and features used\n\n     b) Device & Technical Data\n        - IP address (used to infer approximate geographic location)\n        - Device type, operating system, browser type and version\n        - Screen resolution and language settings\n        - Referring URL and exit pages\n\n     c) Cookies & Similar Technologies We use cookies, web beacons, local storage, and similar technologies. See Section 7 (Cookies) for full details.\n\n1.3  Information from Third Parties\n\n     a) Social Login Providers (Google, Apple, etc.) If you register or log in via a third-party identity provider, we receive your name, email address, and profile picture as permitted by your settings with that provider.\n\n     b) Payment Processors & Fraud Detection Services We may receive risk scores, chargeback alerts, or identity-verification results from our payment partners.\n\n     c) Analytics & Advertising Partners Aggregated or pseudonymous data to help us understand Platform usage and display relevant promotions (subject to your consent preferences).\n\n2. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION\n\nWe use the information we collect for the following purposes:\n\n  2.1  Platform Operation & Order Fulfilment\n       - Create and manage your account\n       - Process payments and deliver Digital Products\n       - Send transaction confirmations, receipts, and order-status updates\n       - Provide customer support and resolve disputes\n\n  2.2  Safety, Security & Fraud Prevention\n       - Verify user identity and age\n       - Detect, investigate, and prevent fraudulent transactions, unauthorised access, and other illegal activities\n       - Comply with anti-money-laundering (AML) and know-your-customer (KYC) obligations where required by law\n\n  2.3  Legal Compliance\n       - Meet obligations under applicable laws and regulations\n       - Respond to lawful requests from government authorities\n       - Enforce our Terms of Service and other agreements\n\n  2.4  Platform Improvement\n       - Analyse usage patterns to improve features and user experience\n       - Conduct A/B testing and internal research\n       - Debug technical issues\n\n  2.5  Marketing & Communications (with Consent)\n       - Send promotional offers, newsletters, and product announcements\n       - Personalise content and recommendations\n       - You may opt out of marketing emails at any time (see Section 8)\n\n  2.6  Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR / applicable law)\n       - Contract performance (processing orders, managing accounts)\n       - Legal obligation (tax, AML/KYC compliance)\n       - Legitimate interests (fraud prevention, security, analytics)\n       - Consent (marketing communications, non-essential cookies)\n\n3. HOW WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION\n\nWe do not sell your personal information. We may share it in the following limited circumstances:\n\n  3.1  Service Providers We engage trusted third-party vendors who process data on our behalf, including:\n       - Payment processors (e.g., Razorpay, Stripe, PayPal)\n       - Cloud hosting and infrastructure providers\n       - Email and SMS delivery platforms\n       - Fraud detection and identity verification services\n       - Customer support software providers\n       - Analytics providers (e.g., Google Analytics)\n\n       All service providers are contractually bound to use data only as directed by us and to maintain appropriate security measures.\n\n  3.2  Business Transfers In the event of a merger, acquisition, asset sale, or bankruptcy proceeding, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction. We will notify you via email and/or a prominent notice on the Platform before your data is transferred and becomes subject to a different privacy policy.\n\n  3.3  Legal Requirements & Protection of Rights We may disclose information when we believe, in good faith, that disclosure is necessary to:\n       - Comply with a legal obligation, court order, or government request\n       - Protect the safety of any person\n       - Detect or prevent fraud or security threats\n       - Enforce our Terms of Service\n\n  3.4  Aggregated / De-identified Data We may share anonymised, aggregated statistics (e.g., "10,000 users purchased gift cards this month") that cannot reasonably identify any individual.\n\n4. DATA RETENTION\n\nWe retain personal information for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes described in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law:\n\n  - Account data: retained for the life of your account plus 3 years after account closure, to resolve disputes and comply with legal obligations.\n  - Transaction records: retained for a minimum of 7 years for tax and financial-reporting purposes.\n  - Support communications: retained for 2 years after the ticket is closed.\n  - Marketing data: retained until you withdraw consent or unsubscribe.\n  - Server / access logs: retained for 90 days, unless required longer for a security investigation.\n\nWhen data is no longer needed it is securely deleted or anonymised.\n\n5. SECURITY\n\nWe implement industry-standard technical and organisational measures to protect your information, including:\n\n  - TLS/SSL encryption for all data in transit\n  - AES-256 encryption for sensitive data at rest\n  - Bcrypt hashing of passwords\n  - Role-based access controls limiting who can access personal data\n  - Regular security audits and penetration testing\n  - PCI-DSS compliance for payment-card data (handled by processors)\n  - Two-factor authentication options for user accounts\n\nNo method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security. In the event of a data breach, we will notify affected users and relevant authorities as required by law.\n\n6. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS\n\nInfinity Kredits operates globally. Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than the country in which you reside. These countries may have data-protection laws that differ from those of your country.\n\nWhere required, we ensure such transfers comply with applicable law through mechanisms such as Standard Contractual Clauses, adequacy decisions, or other approved transfer tools.\n\n7. COOKIES & TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES\n\n  7.1  Types of Cookies We Use\n\n       - Strictly Necessary Cookies: Required for the Platform to function (e.g., session authentication, shopping cart). Cannot be disabled.\n       - Functional Cookies: Remember your preferences (e.g., language, saved addresses).\n       - Analytics Cookies: Help us understand how visitors use the Platform.\n       - Marketing Cookies: Used to deliver relevant advertisements (only with your consent).\n\n  7.2  Managing Cookies You can control cookies through your browser settings or our Cookie Preference Centre (accessible from any page footer). Disabling certain cookies may affect Platform functionality.\n\n  7.3  Third-Party Tracking Our Platform may contain links to third-party websites or services that have their own privacy and cookie policies. We are not responsible for those third parties\' practices.\n\n8. YOUR RIGHTS & CHOICES\n\nDepending on your location, you may have the following rights:\n\n  8.1  Access \u2014 Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.\n  8.2  Correction \u2014 Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.\n  8.3  Deletion \u2014 Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten"), subject to legal retention obligations.\n  8.4  Restriction \u2014 Request that we restrict processing of your data in certain circumstances.\n  8.5  Portability \u2014 Request that we provide your data in a structured, machine-readable format.\n  8.6  Objection \u2014 Object to processing based on our legitimate interests or for direct marketing purposes.\n  8.7  Withdraw Consent \u2014 Where processing is based on consent, you may withdraw it at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing.\n  8.8  Do Not Sell / Share (CCPA) \u2014 California residents have the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information.\n\n  To exercise any of these rights, contact us at: infinitykredits@gmail.com We will respond within 30 days (or as required by applicable law).\n\n  Marketing Opt-Out: Click "Unsubscribe" in any marketing email, or update your preferences in Account Settings > Notifications.\n\n9. CHILDREN\'S PRIVACY\n\nOur Platform is not directed to individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 16. If we become aware that we have collected data from a minor under 16 without verified parental consent, we will delete that information promptly.\n\nFor full details on our age restrictions and minor-safety practices, please refer to our Minor Safety Policy.\n\nIf you believe a child under 16 has provided us with personal information, please contact us at: infinitykredits@gmail.com\n\n10. THIRD-PARTY LINKS & SERVICES\n\nOur Platform may contain links to third-party websites, game platforms, or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those third parties. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any third-party services you access through our Platform.\n\n11. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\n\nWe may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make material changes, we will notify you by:\n  - Sending an email to the address associated with your account, and/or\n  - Displaying a prominent notice on the Platform.\n\nThe updated Policy will be effective as of the "Last Updated" date at the top. Your continued use of the Platform after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.\n\n12. CONTACT US\n\nIf you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n  We aim to respond to all privacy-related inquiries within 30 days.\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.N_=new A.bK(B.d2,["MINOR SAFETY POLICY","Youth safety, limits and protections","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 MINOR SAFETY POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nThe safety and protection of minors is a core value at Infinity Kredits. This Minor Safety Policy establishes strict rules regarding the eligibility of minors to access or use our Platform, and sets out the measures we take to keep young people safe.\n\nPlease read this Policy carefully. By using our Platform you confirm that you meet the minimum age requirement described below.\n\n1. MINIMUM AGE REQUIREMENT \u2014 NO USERS UNDER 16\n\n1.1  USERS MUST BE AT LEAST 16 YEARS OLD\n\n     YOU MUST BE AT LEAST SIXTEEN (16) YEARS OF AGE TO CREATE AN ACCOUNT, BROWSE, OR MAKE ANY PURCHASE ON THE INFINITY KREDITS PLATFORM.\n\n     We do not allow any person under the age of 16 to:\n       - Register an account\n       - Browse or access age-restricted product listings\n       - Purchase Digital Products (in-game currency, coins, gift cards, or any other digital goods)\n       - Participate in promotions, referral programmes, or reward schemes\n       - Submit any personal information through our Platform\n\n1.2  USERS AGED 16\u201317 ("Young Users")\n\n     Users aged 16 or 17 ("Young Users") may access the Platform and make purchases only where permitted by the laws of their country or region. In jurisdictions where the age of majority is 18, Young Users may be required to obtain verifiable parental/guardian consent before completing a purchase. We reserve the right to request proof of such consent at any time.\n\n1.3  USERS AGED 18+\n\n     Users who are 18 years of age or older are considered adults for the purposes of this Platform and may use all features without parental restriction, subject to our Terms of Service.\n\n2. AGE VERIFICATION\n\n2.1  Declaration at Registration All users must declare their date of birth during account registration. By submitting a date of birth, you confirm that the information is accurate and that you meet the minimum age requirement.\n\n2.2  Enhanced Verification We reserve the right to implement additional age-verification steps, including but not limited to:\n       - Upload of a government-issued identity document (passport, national ID, driver\'s licence)\n       - Third-party age-verification services\n       - Credit-card verification checks\n\n2.3  Suspected Underage Use If we have reasonable grounds to believe a user is under 16, we will:\n       a) Immediately suspend the account pending verification\n       b) Halt all pending transactions associated with that account\n       c) Request proof of age within 7 days\n       d) Permanently close the account and refund any recent purchases if proof of age is not provided or confirms the user is under 16\n\n2.4  False Declaration Providing a false date of birth or otherwise misrepresenting your age to gain access to the Platform is a material breach of our Terms of Service and may result in:\n       - Immediate and permanent account termination\n       - Forfeiture of account balances and pending orders\n       - Reporting to relevant authorities where legally required\n\n3. PARENTAL / GUARDIAN RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n3.1  Parents and guardians are responsible for monitoring their children\'s online activity and ensuring that individuals under 16 do not access our Platform.\n\n3.2  If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child (under 16) has created an account or made a purchase on our Platform without your knowledge, please contact us immediately:\n\n       Email:  infinitykredits@gmail.com Subject: "Underage Account \u2013 Immediate Assistance"\n\n     We will investigate and, if confirmed, close the account and process a full refund of any purchases made by the minor.\n\n3.3  Parental Controls We encourage parents and guardians to:\n       - Enable device-level parental controls\n       - Review bank or card statements for unrecognised transactions\n       - Discuss responsible online spending with their children\n\n3.4  We accept no liability for purchases made by a minor using a parent\'s or guardian\'s account credentials without permission. However, we will make reasonable efforts to assist with refund requests in such cases (see our Payments & Refund Policy for details).\n\n4. PROTECTION OF MINORS\' DATA\n\n4.1  We do not knowingly collect, store, or process personal information from any person under the age of 16.\n\n4.2  If we discover that we have inadvertently collected data from a person under 16, we will:\n       - Immediately delete all associated personal data\n       - Close the account\n       - Notify relevant authorities if required by law (e.g., under GDPR, COPPA, or the Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 in India)\n\n4.3  Our data handling practices for Young Users (16\u201317) comply with all applicable laws governing the processing of data of minors, including enhanced consent requirements where mandated.\n\n5. SAFE PLATFORM ENVIRONMENT\n\n5.1  No Targeting of Minors Infinity Kredits does not direct any marketing, advertising, or promotional communications towards users known or reasonably suspected to be under 16.\n\n5.2  Prohibited Content Our Platform does not host or link to content that:\n       - Depicts or exploits minors in any sexual or harmful manner\n       - Facilitates grooming, harassment, or exploitation of minors\n       - Promotes dangerous behaviours to young people\n\n5.3  Reporting Harmful Content If you encounter any content or conduct on our Platform that you believe endangers a minor, please report it immediately:\n\n       Email:    infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls)\n\n     We take all such reports seriously and will respond within 24 hours.\n\n5.4  Cooperation with Authorities Infinity Kredits will cooperate fully with law-enforcement agencies and child-protection organisations investigating any suspected harm to minors in connection with our Platform.\n\n6. LEGAL FRAMEWORK\n\nThis Policy has been designed to comply with, among other regulations:\n\n  - Children\'s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA), USA\n  - General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), EU/UK \u2014 Article 8\n  - Digital Personal Data Protection Act (DPDPA) 2023, India\n  - UN Convention on the Rights of the Child\n  - Age Appropriate Design Code (AADC / "Children\'s Code"), UK\n  - Any other applicable national or regional child-safety laws\n\n7. ENFORCEMENT & VIOLATIONS\n\n  7.1  Accounts confirmed as belonging to users under 16 will be closed immediately without appeal.\n\n  7.2  Refunds for underage accounts will be issued to the original payment method within 10 business days of verification, subject to our Payments & Refund Policy.\n\n  7.3  We reserve the right to take legal action against any individual who facilitates or enables a minor to access the Platform unlawfully.\n\n8. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\n\nWe may update this Policy periodically to reflect changes in law or our practices. Material changes will be communicated via email and/or a notice on the Platform. Continued use of the Platform following any update constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.\n\n9. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n  For urgent child-safety concerns, please mark your email subject line:\n  "URGENT \u2013 MINOR SAFETY"\n\n  We are committed to responding to all minor-safety reports within 24 hours.\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.MW=new A.bK(B.d2,["PAYMENTS & REFUND POLICY","Digital merchandise rules","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 PAYMENTS & REFUND POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nThis Payments & Refund Policy governs all financial transactions made through the Infinity Kredits Platform, including the purchase of in-game currency, app coins, gift cards, and other digital products ("Digital Products"). Please read this Policy carefully before making any purchase.\n\nBy completing a transaction on our Platform, you agree to the terms set out in this Policy.\n\n1. SUPPORTED PAYMENT METHODS\n\nInfinity Kredits accepts the following payment methods (availability may vary by country):\n\n  1.1  Credit & Debit Cards\n       - Visa, Mastercard, American Express, Rupay\n\n  1.2  Digital Wallets & UPI (India)\n       - UPI (Unified Payments Interface)\n       - Paytm, PhonePe, Google Pay, Amazon Pay\n\n  1.3  Net Banking\n       - All major nationalised and private banks (India)\n\n  1.4  International Payment Methods\n       - PayPal\n       - Stripe-supported methods\n\n  1.5  Platform Gift Cards & Wallet Credits\n       - Infinity Kredits Wallet Balance\n       - Infinity Kredits Gift Cards (platform-issued)\n\nWe reserve the right to add, remove, or modify supported payment methods at any time. All payment processing is handled by PCI-DSS-compliant third-party payment processors. We do not store raw card details on our servers.\n\n2. PRICING & CURRENCY\n\n  2.1  All prices displayed on the Platform are inclusive of applicable taxes (GST in India, VAT elsewhere) unless explicitly stated otherwise.\n\n  2.2  Prices are denominated in the currency displayed at checkout. International customers may see charges in a foreign currency; your bank or card issuer may apply conversion fees for which Infinity Kredits is not responsible.\n\n  2.3  We reserve the right to change prices at any time. Price changes will not affect orders already confirmed and paid.\n\n  2.4  Promotional or discounted prices are valid only during the stated promotion period and cannot be applied retroactively.\n\n  2.5  All purchases are subject to applicable taxes as required by law. Tax amounts are calculated at checkout based on your billing address and displayed before you complete payment.\n\n3. ORDER PROCESSING & DELIVERY\n\n  3.1  Digital products are typically delivered instantly or within minutes of successful payment confirmation. Delivery methods include:\n         - Credited directly to your Infinity Kredits account balance\n         - Displayed on-screen and emailed to your registered email address\n         - Sent to your registered phone number via SMS (where applicable)\n\n  3.2  In rare cases, delivery may take up to 24 hours due to:\n         - Payment verification delays\n         - System maintenance\n         - High-volume periods\n\n  3.3  If you have not received your Digital Product within 24 hours of a confirmed payment, please contact infinitykredits@gmail.com\n\n  3.4  Orders are only considered confirmed once payment is successfully authorised and captured. A pending or failed transaction does not constitute a confirmed order.\n\n4. REFUND POLICY\n\nIMPORTANT NOTICE: Due to the immediate digital delivery nature of our products, all sales are generally final. However, we provide refunds in the specific circumstances described below.\n\n  4.1  ELIGIBLE REFUND SITUATIONS\n\n       a) Non-Delivery You are eligible for a full refund if your Digital Product was not delivered within 24 hours of a confirmed payment and you have notified us within 7 days of the purchase date.\n\n       b) Incorrect Product Delivered If you received a Digital Product materially different from what was described and shown at the time of purchase (e.g., wrong game currency denomination, wrong gift card brand), you are entitled to either:\n            - A replacement of the correct product, or\n            - A full refund if a replacement cannot be provided within 3 business days\n\n       c) Duplicate Charge If your payment method was charged more than once for a single order due to a technical error, the duplicate charge(s) will be refunded in full within 5\u20137 business days.\n\n       d) Unauthorised Transaction If you believe a transaction was made without your authorisation, contact us immediately. We will investigate and, where confirmed, refund the charge. You must also report the unauthorised transaction to your bank or card issuer.\n\n       e) Underage Purchases Purchases confirmed as having been made by a user under 16 years of age will be refunded in full. See our Minor Safety Policy for details.\n\n       f) Platform Error If a technical fault on our Platform caused an incorrect quantity, price, or product to be charged or delivered, we will correct the error and issue a full or partial refund as appropriate.\n\n  4.2  NON-REFUNDABLE SITUATIONS\n\n       The following are NOT eligible for refunds:\n\n       a) Change of Mind We do not issue refunds because you changed your mind after a Digital Product has been successfully delivered.\n\n       b) Product Already Used / Redeemed Gift cards, codes, or in-game currency that have been redeemed, activated, or applied to a game/application account are non-refundable under any circumstances.\n\n       c) Bans or Restrictions by Third-Party Platforms If a game publisher, app developer, or third-party platform suspends or bans your account, you are not entitled to a refund for currency or products previously delivered to that account.\n\n       d) Dissatisfaction with Third-Party Game/App We are not responsible for changes made by third-party developers to their games or applications (e.g., game updates, feature removals). Such changes do not entitle you to a refund.\n\n       e) Incorrect Information Provided by User If you provided incorrect details at checkout (e.g., wrong game username, wrong region) and the product was delivered based on that information, we are not obligated to refund or reissue the product. We may, at our sole discretion, attempt to assist.\n\n       f) Promotional / Bonus Credits Bonus credits, promotional coins, or free items awarded alongside a purchase have no cash value and cannot be refunded.\n\n  4.3  PARTIAL REFUNDS In cases where a partial refund is warranted (e.g., partial delivery), we will refund only the amount corresponding to the undelivered portion.\n\n5. HOW TO REQUEST A REFUND\n\n  5.1  Submit a refund request by:\n         - Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com\n         - WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls)\n         - In-app:    Account > Order History > [Order] > Request Refund\n\n  5.2  Your request must include:\n         - Order ID / Transaction Reference Number\n         - Registered email address\n         - Reason for refund request\n         - Supporting evidence where applicable (screenshots, error messages)\n\n  5.3  Refund Request Deadline:\n       Refund requests must be submitted within SEVEN (7) calendar days of the purchase date. Requests submitted after this window will not be processed except in cases of documented fraud or legal obligation.\n\n  5.4  Processing Times:\n         - We will acknowledge your request within 2 business days.\n         - We will issue a decision within 5 business days of receiving all required information.\n         - Approved refunds will be credited as follows:\n             Credit / Debit Card:  5\u201310 business days UPI / Net Banking:    2\u20135 business days Digital Wallets:      1\u20133 business days Infinity Kredits Wallet: Instant\n\n  5.5  Refunds are issued to the original payment method only. We do not issue refunds via alternative payment methods, cash, or cheque.\n\n6. CHARGEBACKS & DISPUTES\n\n  6.1  We encourage customers to contact us before initiating a chargeback with their bank or payment provider. Most issues can be resolved quickly and amicably through our support team.\n\n  6.2  If you initiate a chargeback without first contacting us, or if we determine a chargeback is fraudulent, we reserve the right to:\n         - Suspend or permanently terminate your account\n         - Revoke any Digital Products delivered\n         - Pursue recovery of the disputed amount through legal means\n\n  6.3  Chargeback fraud (i.e., falsely claiming a transaction was unauthorised after receiving and using a Digital Product) constitutes fraud and may be reported to law-enforcement authorities.\n\n7. TAXES & INVOICING\n\n  7.1  Applicable taxes (including GST, VAT, and digital services taxes) are calculated at checkout and displayed before payment.\n\n  7.2  A digital receipt is automatically emailed to your registered email address after every successful transaction.\n\n  7.3  For tax-compliant invoices (e.g., with GSTIN), please submit a request via infinitykredits@gmail.com within 30 days of purchase.\n\n8. FAILED & PENDING TRANSACTIONS\n\n  8.1  If a transaction fails, no charge will be applied. If your bank shows a temporary hold ("pending charge"), this will typically be released within 3\u20135 business days without any action required.\n\n  8.2  If you were charged but did not receive a confirmation email or order, contact us immediately at infinitykredits@gmail.com with your transaction reference number.\n\n9. WALLET BALANCE & CREDITS\n\n  9.1  Infinity Kredits Wallet balances have no cash value and cannot be withdrawn or transferred to a bank account.\n\n  9.2  Wallet credits expire 12 months from the date of last activity on your account, unless otherwise stated.\n\n  9.3  Unused Wallet balances at the time of account closure are forfeited and not refundable, except where required by applicable law.\n\n10. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n  Support Hours: Monday\u2013Saturday, 9:00 AM \u2013 6:00 PM IST\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.MY=new A.bK(B.d2,["ACCEPTABLE USE POLICY","Platform rules and guidelines","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 ACCEPTABLE USE POLICY (AUP) Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nThis Acceptable Use Policy ("AUP") sets out the rules for how you may use the Infinity Kredits Platform. It applies to all users, visitors, and anyone interacting with our services. This AUP supplements and should be read alongside our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy.\n\nBy accessing the Platform, you agree to comply with this AUP. Violations may result in suspension or permanent termination of your account.\n\n1. PERMITTED USES\n\nYou may use the Platform to:\n\n  1.1  Browse and purchase Digital Products for your own personal use.\n  1.2  Manage your Account, view your order history, and contact support.\n  1.3  Redeem gift cards and digital codes for their stated purpose.\n  1.4  Participate in official promotions and loyalty programmes.\n\n2. PROHIBITED USES\n\nYou MUST NOT use the Platform to:\n\n  2.1  ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES\n       - Engage in, facilitate, or promote any illegal activity\n       - Violate any applicable local, national, or international law\n       - Use the Platform as a vehicle for money laundering or terrorism financing\n       - Purchase Digital Products with stolen or fraudulently obtained payment credentials\n\n  2.2  FRAUD & ABUSE\n       - Submit false, misleading, or fraudulent purchase requests\n       - Exploit pricing errors or system glitches to obtain products below their intended price\n       - File false chargeback or dispute claims\n       - Misrepresent your identity, age, or location\n       - Create multiple accounts to abuse promotions or referral schemes\n\n  2.3  SECURITY VIOLATIONS\n       - Attempt to gain unauthorised access to the Platform, its servers, databases, or other user accounts\n       - Conduct or facilitate denial-of-service (DoS/DDoS) attacks\n       - Introduce viruses, malware, trojans, or other malicious code\n       - Probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of the Platform without our prior written authorisation (see Responsible Disclosure, Section 5)\n       - Bypass, disable, or circumvent any authentication or security measure\n\n  2.4  AUTOMATED ACCESS\n       - Use bots, scrapers, crawlers, or automated tools to access, collect data from, or interact with the Platform without consent\n       - Artificially generate traffic, clicks, or transactions\n\n  2.5  HARMFUL CONTENT\n       - Post, transmit, or distribute content that is defamatory, obscene, hateful, or discriminatory\n       - Harass, threaten, or intimidate other users or our staff\n       - Impersonate any person, entity, or brand\n\n  2.6  COMMERCIAL EXPLOITATION\n       - Resell Digital Products purchased on the Platform for commercial gain without our explicit written permission\n       - Use Platform data or content for competing commercial purposes\n\n  2.7  MINOR EXPLOITATION\n       - Allow or facilitate access to the Platform by users under 16 years of age\n       - Purchase Digital Products on behalf of a known minor without appropriate supervision\n\n3. CONSEQUENCES OF VIOLATION\n\nIf we determine, in our sole discretion, that you have violated this AUP:\n\n  3.1  We may immediately suspend or permanently terminate your Account.\n  3.2  We may cancel pending orders and revoke delivered Digital Products.\n  3.3  We may forfeit any Account balance, credits, or pending refunds.\n  3.4  We may report violations to law-enforcement authorities.\n  3.5  We may pursue civil or criminal legal action as permitted by law.\n  3.6  We may retain and share information with payment networks for fraud prevention purposes.\n\n4. REPORTING VIOLATIONS\n\nIf you become aware of any violation of this AUP by another user or a third party, please report it to us:\n\n  Email:    infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls)\n\nWe will investigate all reports and take appropriate action. Reports can be made anonymously.\n\n5. RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE (SECURITY RESEARCHERS)\n\nWe welcome good-faith security research. If you believe you have found a security vulnerability in the Platform, please:\n\n  - Do NOT exploit the vulnerability or access user data\n  - Report it promptly and confidentially to: infinitykredits@gmail.com\n  - Provide sufficient detail for us to reproduce and address the issue\n\nWe commit to:\n  - Acknowledging your report within 5 business days\n  - Investigating and resolving valid reports\n  - Not taking legal action against good-faith security researchers who comply with these guidelines\n\n6. AMENDMENTS\n\nWe may update this AUP at any time. Continued use of the Platform after an updated AUP is posted constitutes your acceptance of the changes.\n\n7. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.MZ=new A.bK(B.d2,["ANTI-FRAUD POLICY","Protecting against financial abuse","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 ANTI-FRAUD POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nInfinity Kredits is committed to maintaining a secure, trustworthy marketplace for all users. Fraud harms our customers, our platform, and the integrity of the digital-goods ecosystem. This Anti-Fraud Policy outlines our approach to detecting, preventing, and responding to fraudulent activity.\n\n1. WHAT CONSTITUTES FRAUD\n\nFraud includes, but is not limited to:\n\n  1.1  Payment Fraud\n       - Using stolen, cloned, or unauthorised credit/debit cards or bank accounts to make purchases\n       - Using fraudulently obtained UPI credentials or wallet accounts\n       - Using compromised payment tokens or credentials\n\n  1.2  Chargeback Fraud ("Friendly Fraud")\n       - Initiating chargebacks after successfully receiving and using Digital Products ("buyer\'s remorse fraud")\n       - Filing false "item not received" claims when products were delivered\n\n  1.3  Identity Fraud\n       - Creating accounts with false names, email addresses, or dates of birth\n       - Impersonating other users or third parties\n       - Using synthetic identities to evade account bans\n\n  1.4  Promotion Abuse\n       - Creating multiple accounts to exploit welcome offers, discount codes, or referral bonuses\n       - Sharing, selling, or misusing promotional codes\n\n  1.5  Resale Fraud\n       - Purchasing large volumes of Digital Products for unauthorised commercial resale\n\n  1.6  Account Takeover\n       - Gaining unauthorised access to another user\'s account to make purchases or extract Digital Products\n\n2. FRAUD DETECTION MEASURES\n\nWe employ multi-layered fraud detection systems, including:\n\n  2.1  Real-Time Transaction Monitoring All transactions are screened against fraud rules and risk models at the time of purchase. Suspicious transactions may be:\n         - Flagged for manual review\n         - Placed on hold pending verification\n         - Automatically declined\n\n  2.2  Identity & Age Verification We verify user identity and age at registration and/or at the point of high-value transactions.\n\n  2.3  Device & Behavioural Analysis We monitor device fingerprints, IP addresses, login patterns, and behavioural signals to detect anomalies.\n\n  2.4  Payment Network Data We receive fraud signals from payment networks and processors (including velocity checks and bin risk scoring).\n\n  2.5  Third-Party Fraud Prevention Services We may use specialist third-party services to supplement our internal fraud controls.\n\n3. CONSEQUENCES OF FRAUDULENT ACTIVITY\n\nIf fraud is detected or reasonably suspected:\n\n  3.1  We will immediately suspend the associated Account(s) pending investigation.\n  3.2  We will cancel all pending orders and revoke any recently delivered Digital Products where technically possible.\n  3.3  We will report the fraud to the relevant payment networks, banks, and law-enforcement agencies.\n  3.4  We will pursue recovery of losses through all available legal means, including civil litigation.\n  3.5  Confirmed fraudulent accounts will be permanently banned. Associated device IDs, IP addresses, and payment methods may be blacklisted.\n  3.6  We may share information about confirmed fraud with industry anti-fraud consortia and payment processors to protect other merchants.\n\n4. YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n  4.1  You are responsible for keeping your Account credentials secure.\n  4.2  You must contact us immediately at infinitykredits@gmail.com if you suspect your Account has been compromised.\n  4.3  You must never share your Account login, payment details, or verification codes (OTPs) with anyone \u2014 including people claiming to be Infinity Kredits staff. We will NEVER ask for your password.\n  4.4  You must not facilitate or assist any third party in committing fraud against the Platform.\n\n5. REPORTING FRAUD\n\nIf you suspect fraudulent activity \u2014 by another user or involving your own Account \u2014 please report it immediately:\n\n  Email:    infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Subject:  "FRAUD REPORT \u2013 [brief description]"\n\nWe investigate all fraud reports promptly. Reports may be made anonymously.\n\n6. COOPERATION WITH AUTHORITIES\n\nInfinity Kredits cooperates fully with law-enforcement agencies, financial intelligence units, and regulatory bodies investigating fraud, money laundering, and related financial crimes. We will disclose account and transaction data as required by valid legal process.\n\n7. ANTI-MONEY-LAUNDERING (AML) COMMITMENT\n\n  7.1  We do not knowingly facilitate money laundering or the financing of terrorism.\n  7.2  Where required by applicable law, we may conduct Know Your Customer (KYC) checks and report suspicious transaction activity to the Financial Intelligence Unit (FIU-IND) or equivalent body.\n  7.3  Transactions that exhibit money-laundering patterns (e.g., structured purchases designed to evade reporting thresholds) will be refused and reported.\n\n8. AMENDMENTS\n\nWe may update this Policy as fraud risks and our practices evolve. Material changes will be communicated via the Platform.\n\n9. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.N1=new A.bK(B.d2,["COOKIE POLICY","Tracking and analytics","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 COOKIE POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nThis Cookie Policy explains how Infinity Kredits ("we," "us," "our") uses cookies and similar tracking technologies when you visit our website or use our mobile application (the "Platform"). It should be read alongside our Privacy Policy.\n\nBy continuing to use the Platform after seeing our cookie notice, you consent to our use of non-essential cookies as described below.\n\n1. WHAT ARE COOKIES?\n\nCookies are small text files placed on your device (computer, phone, or tablet) by a website when you visit it. They allow the website to remember information about your visit, such as your preferred language or login status.\n\nSimilar technologies we use include:\n  - Web Beacons (pixel tags): Tiny images embedded in pages or emails used to track whether content has been viewed.\n  - Local Storage / Session Storage: Browser-based storage for app state.\n  - Device Fingerprinting: Technical identifiers used for fraud detection.\n\n2. TYPES OF COOKIES WE USE\n\n  2.1  STRICTLY NECESSARY COOKIES Purpose:  Essential for the Platform to operate. These include session authentication, shopping cart functionality, and security features. Consent:  Not required. These cannot be disabled without breaking the Platform. Examples: Login session, CSRF protection token, payment session.\n\n  2.2  FUNCTIONAL COOKIES Purpose:  Remember your preferences and personalise your experience. Consent:  Enabled by default; you may disable them. Examples: Language preference, saved delivery address, theme settings.\n\n  2.3  ANALYTICS COOKIES Purpose:  Help us understand how visitors interact with the Platform so we can improve it. Data is aggregated and anonymised. Consent:  Requires your consent. Examples: Google Analytics (page views, session duration, bounce rate).\n\n  2.4  MARKETING / ADVERTISING COOKIES Purpose:  Track browsing behaviour to display relevant ads and promotional content across the web. Consent:  Requires your explicit consent. Examples: Google Ads remarketing, Meta Pixel (where used).\n\n  2.5  FRAUD DETECTION COOKIES Purpose:  Detect suspicious behaviour and prevent fraudulent transactions. These are strictly necessary for security. Consent:  Not required. Examples: Device fingerprint hash, payment-risk score tokens.\n\n3. THIRD-PARTY COOKIES\n\nSome cookies are set by third-party services embedded in our Platform:\n\n  Provider            | Purpose                  | Type\n  --------------------|--------------------------|--------------------- Google Analytics    | Usage analytics          | Analytics Google Ads          | Advertising              | Marketing Razorpay / Stripe   | Payment processing       | Strictly Necessary Facebook / Meta     | Social sharing / ads     | Marketing (if used) Cloudflare          | Security / CDN           | Strictly Necessary\n\nThese third parties have their own privacy and cookie policies. We encourage you to review them directly.\n\n4. HOW LONG DO COOKIES LAST?\n\n  - Session Cookies: Deleted when you close your browser.\n  - Persistent Cookies: Remain on your device for a set period:\n      - Functional cookies:  Up to 1 year\n      - Analytics cookies:   Up to 2 years\n      - Marketing cookies:   Up to 1 year\n\n5. HOW TO MANAGE COOKIES\n\n  5.1  Cookie Preference Centre You can change your cookie preferences at any time using the Cookie Preference Centre, accessible via the footer link on our website.\n\n  5.2  Browser Settings You can configure your browser to block or delete cookies:\n         - Chrome:  Settings > Privacy & Security > Cookies\n         - Firefox: Settings > Privacy & Security > Cookies and Site Data\n         - Safari:  Settings > Safari > Privacy & Security\n         - Edge:    Settings > Cookies and Site Permissions\n\n       Note: Blocking strictly necessary cookies will prevent the Platform from functioning properly.\n\n  5.3  Opt-Out Tools\n       - Google Analytics: https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout\n       - Google Ads: https://adssettings.google.com\n       - Your Online Choices (EU): https://www.youronlinechoices.eu\n       - Network Advertising Initiative: https://optout.networkadvertising.org\n\n6. UPDATES TO THIS POLICY\n\nWe may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last Updated" date at the top. Material changes will also be communicated via a notice on the Platform.\n\n7. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
B.N0=new A.bK(B.d2,["INTELLECTUAL RIGHTS POLICY","Copyright and ownership","INFINITY KREDITS \u2014 INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY POLICY Effective Date: May 25, 2026 Last Updated:   May 25, 2026 Version:        1.0",'INTRODUCTION\n\nThis Intellectual Property Policy describes how Infinity Kredits protects its own intellectual property and how it handles claims that content or products on the Platform infringe the intellectual property rights of third parties.\n\n1. INFINITY KREDITS INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\n\n  1.1  All content, materials, and technology on the Platform \u2014 including the Infinity Kredits name, logo, brand identity, website design, software code, database structures, product descriptions, and graphic assets \u2014 are the property of Infinity Kredits or its licensors and are protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual-property laws.\n\n  1.2  The "Infinity Kredits" name and logo are trademarks of the Company. You may not use them without our prior written permission.\n\n  1.3  Nothing in these Terms grants you any ownership rights in our intellectual property. You receive only the limited licence to use the Platform described in our Terms of Service.\n\n2. THIRD-PARTY INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\n\n  2.1  Game and application assets (including in-game currency names, icons, and branding) are the intellectual property of their respective developers and publishers. Infinity Kredits uses such references only to identify compatible products and does not claim ownership.\n\n  2.2  Gift card brands, logos, and trademarks are the property of the respective issuing companies. Use of their marks on our Platform is for identification and resale purposes only.\n\n  2.3  Infinity Kredits is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or an official partner of any game developer, publisher, or gift-card issuer unless explicitly stated.\n\n3. COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT CLAIMS (DMCA / TAKEDOWN PROCEDURE)\n\n  3.1  If you believe that content on our Platform infringes your copyright, please send a written notice to our designated agent containing:\n\n       a) A description of the copyrighted work you claim has been infringed;\n       b) A description of the allegedly infringing material and its location on our Platform (URL or screenshot);\n       c) Your contact information (name, address, phone, email);\n       d) A statement that you have a good-faith belief that the use is not authorised by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law;\n       e) A statement that the information in the notice is accurate, and under penalty of perjury, that you are authorised to act on behalf of the copyright owner;\n       f) Your physical or electronic signature.\n\n  3.2  Send copyright notices to:\n       Email:   infinitykredits@gmail.com Subject: "Copyright Infringement Notice"\n\n  3.3  We will investigate valid notices and respond within 10 business days. Confirmed infringing content will be removed promptly.\n\n  3.4  Counter-Notices: If you believe content was removed in error, you may submit a counter-notice with the information required by law. Counter-notices should be sent to the same address.\n\n4. TRADEMARK INFRINGEMENT CLAIMS\n\n  4.1  If you believe content on our Platform infringes your trademark rights, please contact us at infinitykredits@gmail.com with:\n         - Identification of the trademark at issue\n         - Your ownership or authorisation to act\n         - Description of the alleged infringing use\n         - Your contact information\n\n  4.2  We will review all trademark claims and respond within 10 business days.\n\n5. REPEAT INFRINGERS\n\nIn appropriate circumstances, Infinity Kredits will terminate the accounts of users who are found to be repeat infringers of intellectual property rights.\n\n6. CONTACT US\n\n  Infinity Kredits Email:     infinitykredits@gmail.com WhatsApp:  +91 95689 02453 (WhatsApp only \u2014 no calls) Address:   Moradabad, 244001, Uttar Pradesh, INDIA\n\n\xa9 2026 Infinity Kredits. All rights reserved. '],t.l)
